Write a Java function to implement the following logic: Given a string str and a non-empty word word, return a version of the original string where all characters are replaced with a plus sign (+), but occurrences of word remain unchanged.

public String plusOut(String str, String word)
{

}

Code:
public String plusOut(String str, String word) {
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    int wordLen = word.length();
    int i = 0;
    while (i < str.length()) {
        int matchLength = 0;
        if (str.substring(i).startsWith(word)) {
            sb.append(word);
            i += wordLen;
        } else {
            while (i < str.length() && matchLength < wordLen && str.charAt(i) != word.charAt(matchLength)) {
                sb.append("+");
                i++;
                matchLength = 0;
            }
            if (i < str.length() && matchLength < wordLen && str.charAt(i) == word.charAt(matchLength)) {
                sb.append(str.charAt(i));
                i++;
                matchLength++;
            }
        }
    }
    return sb.toString();
}

